0on%20Capitol%20Hill.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20measure%20was%20recently%20dropped%20from%20the%20final%20version%20of%20the%20annual%20defense%20bill.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnd%20Hawley%20is%20pointing%20at%20Speaker%20Mike%20Johnson%20and%20Senate%20GOP%20Leader%20Mitch%20McConnell%20over%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20expansion%20and%20reauthorization%20of%20the%20Radiation%20Exposure%20Compensation%20Act%20was%20overwhelmingly%20backed%20by%20the%20Senate%20in%20August%2C%20but%20the%20measure%20was%20stripped%20from%20the%20House%20version%20of%20the%20annual%20defense%20bill%20and%20wasn't%20included%20in%20the%20final%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Republican%20Sen.%20Josh%20Hawley%20of%20Missouri%2C%20the%20measure's%20cosponsor%20and%20one%20of%20its%20biggest%20champions%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%2C%20is%20not%20taking%20the%20change%20lying%20down%2C%20calling%20out%20leaders%20of%20his%20party%20over%20the%20issue%20for%20what%20he%20says%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bbetrayal%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20victims%20affected%20by%20radiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Hawley%20was%20asked%20last%20week%20why%20the%20measure%20was%20removed%20from%20the%20National%20Defense%20Authorization%20Act%20(NDAA)%2C%20he%20pointed%20to%20the%20top%20GOP%20leaders%20in%20Congress%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fpolicy%2Fenergy-environment%2F4350583-republicans-divided-defense-bill-radiation-victims-compensation-mcconnell-johnson-hawley-crapo-schmitt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etelling%20The%20Hill%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Byou%20ought%20to%20ask%26quot%3B%20House%20Speaker%20Mike%20Johnson%20of%20Louisiana%20and%20Senate%20Minority%20Leader%20Mitch%20McConnell%20of%20Kentucky%20about%20the%20exclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHawley%2C%20a%20first-term%20senator%20who's%20up%20for%20reelection%20in%202024%2C%20told%20The%20Hill%20that%20Senate%20Majority%20Leader%20Chuck%20Schumer%20of%20New%20York%20and%20House%20Minority%20Leader%20Hakeem%20Jeffries%20of%20New%20York%20had%20both%20been%20%26quot%3Bsupportive%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20measure%2C%20but%20he%20said%20he%20was%20unclear%20about%20Johnson%20and%20McConnell's%20rationale%20for%20the%20measure%20falling%20out%20of%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMorally%2C%20this%20is%20obscene%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Missourian%20told%20the%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHawley%20cosponsored%20the%20amendment%20with%20fellow%20Missouri%20GOP%20Sen.%20Eric%20Schmitt%2C%20along%20with%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Ben%20Ray%20Luj%C3%A1n%20of%20New%20Mexico%20and%20GOP%20Sen.%20Mike%20Crapo%20of%20Idaho.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20original%201990%20law%20provided%20compensation%20to%20American%20citizens%20who%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20nuclear%20waste%20radiation%20in%20Arizona%2C%20Nevada%2C%20and%20Utah%3B%20the%20reauthorization%20would%20include%20sites%20in%20Colorado%2C%20Missouri%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Guam%2C%20while%20also%20providing%20funds%20for%20an%20additional%2019%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20in%202022%20extended%20the%20law%2C%20but%20that%20extension%20is%20set%20to%20end%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHawley%20in%20the%20past%20has%20pledged%20to%20vote%20against%20and%20block%20the%20NDAA%20if%20it%20did%20not%20include%20the%20reauthorization.%20And%20his%20statements%20last%20week%20only%20affirmed%20his%20continued%20fight%20for%20compensation%20for%20victims%20affected%20by%20radiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20major%20betrayal%20of%20thousands%20and%20thousands%20of%20Missourians%20who%20have%20been%20lied%20to%20and%20ignored%20for%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FHawleyMO%2Fstatus%2F1732528194954068108%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHawley%20wrote%20on%20X%20last%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20also%20a%20betrayal%20of%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20Americans%20made%20sick%20by%20their%20government's%20nuclear%20waste%20who%20have%20rel