%20join%20either%20of%20the%20two%20dominions%20or%20remain%20independent.%20The%20underlying%20principle%20for%20the%20choice%20before%20the%20states%20was%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20and%20the%20geographical%20location%2C%20even%20though%20these%20principles%20were%20not%20binding%20on%20the%20princely%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20legal%20expert%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-article-370-has-not-been-scrapped-but-kashmirs-special-status-has-gone-5880390%2F%5C%22%3EFaizan%20Mustafa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20technically%2C%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20was%20like%20a%20treaty%20between%20two%20sovereign%20countries%20that%20had%20decided%20to%20work%20together.%20The%20maxim%20of%20%3Cem%3Epacta%20sunt%20servanda%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20international%20law%2C%20which%20governs%20contracts%20or%20treaties%20between%20states%2C%20asks%20that%20promises%20must%20be%20honoured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20Viceroy%20of%20the%20British%20empire%2C%20Lord%20Mountbatten%20put%20forward%20before%20the%20rulers%20two%20documents%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20and%20a%20Standstill%20Agreement%2C%20for%20the%20continuance%20for%20the%20time%20being%20of%20agreements%20and%20arrangements%20in%20matters%20of%20common%20concern%20between%20the%20states%20and%20the%20dominion%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10172506%2Fimage-1596-300x213.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10172506%2Fimage-1596-300x213.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10172506%2Fimage-1596.png%20607w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688499%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22213%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMaharaja%20Hari%20and%20Sardar%20Patel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMountbatten%20told%20the%20princes%20on%20July%2025%201947%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CIndian%20independence%20Act%20releases%20the%20States%20from%20all%20their%20obligations%20and%20the%20states%20have%20complete%20freedom%20technically%20and%20legally%20they%20are%20independent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20states%20are%20theoretically%20free%20to%20link%20their%20future%20with%20whichever%20they%20may%20care%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20when%20I%20say%20they%20are%20at%20liberty%20to%20link%20up%20with%20either%20of%20the%20two%20dominions%20may%20I%20point%20out%20that%20there%20are%20certain%20geographical%20compulsions%20which%20cannot%20be%20avoided.%E2%80%9D%20He%20elaborated%20you%20%E2%80%9Ccannot%20run%20away%20from%20the%20dominion%20government%20which%20is%20your%20neighbour%20any%20more%20than%20you%20can%20run%20away%20from%20the%20subject%20for%20who%E2%80%99s%20welfare%20you%20are%20responsible.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20independence%20all%20these%20states%20acceded%20to%20one%20or%20the%20other%20dominion%20as%20per%20the%20arrangement%20except%20Hyderabad%2C%20Junagadh%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJunagadh%20and%20J%26amp%3BK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA.G.%20Noorani%20in%20his%20book%20%E2%80%98The%20Kashmir%20dispute%20%E2%80%93%201947%20to%202012%E2%80%99%20makes%20a%20comparison%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20which%20was%20a%20Muslim%20majority%20State%20ruled%20by%20a%20Hindu%20ruler%20and%20Junagadh%2C%20a%20Hindu%20majority%20ruled%20by%20a%20Muslim%20ruler.%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20prime%20minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20had%20objected%20to%20Junagadh%E2%80%99s%20accession%20to%20Pakistan%20on%20grounds%20that%20the%20population%20of%20Junagadh%20was%2080%25%20Hindu%20and%20batted%20for%20a%20referendum%20under%20impartial%20auspices.%20The%20princely%20state%20was%20surrounded%20on%20all%20of%20its%20land%20borders%20by%20India%2C%20with%20an%20outlet%20onto%20the%20Arabian%20sea.%20Its%20ruler%2C%20Nawab%20Muhammad%20Mahabat%20Khanji%20argued%20that%20Junagadh%20was%20linked%20to%20Pakistan%20by%20sea%20against%20the%20advice%20of%20Mountbatten.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fafter-march-2020-sc-to-hear-pleas-against-abrogation-of-article-370-on-july-11%5C%22%3EKashmir%3A%20Three%20Years%2C%2011%20Months%20After%20Article%20370%20Was%20Scrapped%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20Take%20Up%20Matter%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20position%20was%20that%20Junagadh%20had%20acceded%20to%20Pakistan%20ignoring%20geographical%20considerations%20and%20the%20principle%20of%20religion%20or%20the%20exercise%20of%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people.%20This%20became%20the%20basis%20of%20Indian%20army%E2%80%99s%20military%20intervention%20in%20Junagadh%20to%20wrest%20it%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20and%20the%20Muslim%20ruler%E2%80%99s%20control.%20This%2C%20however%2C%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20hasty%20referendum%20in%20February%201948%20and%20by%20an%20almost%20unanimous%20vote%20the%20people%20showed%20their%20preference%20for%20India.%20Many%20scholars%2C%20however%2C%20have%20observed%20that%20India%20annexed%20Junagadh%20by%20force%20and%20laid%20down%20the%20international%20opinion%20on%20the%20principle%20of%20accession%20%E2%80%93%20geographical%20contiguity%20to%20the%20dominion%20and%20the%20demographics.%20The%20mobilisation%20of%20Indian%20defence%20forces%20in%20the%20lead%20up%20to%20the%20accession%20of%20Junagadh%20in%20November%201947%20and%20the%20management%20of%20violence%20directed%20at%20Junagadh%E2%80%99s%20Muslims%20afterwards%20are%20an%20instance%20of%20the%20forcible%20incorporation%20of%20Indian%20princely%20states%20and%20Indian%20Muslims%20into%20the%20reconstructed%20post-colonial%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMountbatten%20and%20Ayyangar%20both%20agreed%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20geographical%20contiguity%20had%20no%20legal%20standing%20and%20that%20Junagadh%E2%80%99s%20accession%20to%20Pakistan%20was%20strictly%20and%20legally%20correct.%20But%20Sardar%20Patel%20demanded%20that%20the%20matter%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20accession%20should%20be%20decided%20by%20its%20people%20instead%20of%20the%20ruler.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20concluded%20a%20Standstill%20Agreement%20with%20the%20government%20of%20Pakistan%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20maintenance%20of%20the%20existing%20arrangement%20in%20respect%20of%20posts%20and%20telegraphs%20etc%20and%20thus%20it%20was%20open%20to%20Kashmir%20to%20exceed%20to%20either%20of%20the%20two%20dominions%20or%20remain%20independent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHyderabad%2C%20ruled%20by%20a%20Muslim%20leader%20presiding%20over%20a%20Hindu%20majority%20and%20with%20no%20geographical%20link%20to%20Pakistan%2C%20met%20a%20similar%20fate.%20Stephen%20P.%20Cohen%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20vision%20of%20a%20future%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20rubbed%20against%20the%20ambitions%20of%20some%20of%20the%20princes%2C%20with%20the%20result%20that%20the%20rush%20to%20force%20them%20to%20join%20one%20or%20the%20other%20ignited%20several%20significant%20conflicts.%E2%80%9D%20Although%2C%20technically%2C%20the%20decision%20to%20accede%20was%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20ruler%2C%20not%20the%20ruled%2C%20India%20used%20force%20to%20incorporate%20Hyderabad%20and%20Junagadh%2C%20he%20writes.%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ednref3%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkashmirtimes.com%2Farticle-370-understanding-history-legal-contexts-and-why-it-matters%2F%23_edn3%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScholars%20are%20divided%20on%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20the%20decision%20was%20to%20be%20made%20by%20the%20rulers%20or%20the%20ruled.%20The%20will%20of%20the%20latter%2C%20a%20principally%20more%20moral%20option%2C%20could%20be%20asserted%20only%20through%20a%20referendum.%20Whatever%20the%20morality%20of%20the%20question%2C%20India%20could%20not%20have%20applied%20two%20yardsticks%20for%20the%20different%20princely%20states%20awaiting%20a%20decision%20on%20their%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20if%20the%20principle%20of%20geographical%20contiguity%20and%20demographics%20was%20valid%20for%20Junagadh%2C%20could%20a%20different%20yardstick%20be%20applied%20to%20Kashmir.%20The%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20concluded%20a%20Standstill%20Agreement%20with%20the%20government%20of%20Pakistan%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20maintenance%20of%20the%20existing%20arrangement%20in%20respect%20of%20posts%20and%20telegraphs%20etc%20and%20thus%20it%20was%20open%20to%20Kashmir%20to%20exceed%20to%20either%20of%20the%20two%20dominions%20or%20remain%20independent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10172856%2Fimage-1597.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10172856%2Fimage-1597.png%20526w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10172856%2Fimage-1597-189x300.png%20189w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688500%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221356%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESheikh%20Mohammed%20Abdullah%2C%20Jawahar%20Lal%20Nehru%20and%20Badshah%20Khan%20in%20Shalimar%20Garden%2C%20Srinagar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20period%20of%20indecisiveness%20coincided%20with%20several%20other%20almost%20simultaneous%20events%20%E2%80%93%20the%20communal%20troubles%20in%20Jammu%20following%20the%20movement%20of%20refugees%20from%20West%20Punjab%20into%20Jammu%2C%20the%20Poonch%20revolt%20against%20the%20Maharaja%20and%20the%20armed%20tribals%20entering%20the%20state%20with%20the%20connivance%20and%20support%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20authorities%2C%20forcing%20the%20Maharaja%20to%20send%20a%20desperate%20distress%20appeal%20for%20help%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fkashmir-and-manipur-double-standards-of-modis-new-india%5C%22%3EKashmir%20and%20Manipur%3A%20Double%20Standards%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20New%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeriod%20of%20indecisiveness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahatma%20Gandhi%20on%20a%20visit%20to%20the%20state%20in%20August%201947%20said%20that%20the%20will%20of%20the%20Kashmiris%20should%20decide%20the%20fate%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20added%20that%20the%20sooner%20this%20was%20done%20the%20better%20he%20also%20hoped%20that%20the%20question%20would%20be%20decided%20between%20the%20two%20dominions%2C%20the%20Maharaja%20and%20the%20Kashmiris%2C%20elaborating%20that%20%E2%80%9Cif%20the%20four%20could%20come%20to%20a%20joint%20decision%20then%20much%20trouble%20would%20be%20saved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Maharaja%20who%20wanted%20to%20save%20and%20safeguard%20his%20princely%20privileges%20was%20uncomfortable%20in%20signing%20an%20accession%20either%20with%20India%2C%20looking%20towards%20a%20democratic%20and%20anti-feudal%20future%2C%20or%20with%20Pakistan%2C%20with%20its%20Muslim%20majority.%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%2C%20who%20was%20released%20from%20jail%20in%20September%201947%2C%20also%20made%20his%20preference%20publicly%20known%20towards%20independence%2C%20warning%20that%20that%20if%20the%20state%20declares%20accession%20to%20India%20or%20Pakistan%2C%20he%20would%20raise%20the%20banner%20of%20revolt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20period%20of%20indecisiveness%20coincided%20with%20several%20other%20almost%20simultaneous%20events%20%E2%80%93%20the%20communal%20troubles%20in%20Jammu%20following%20the%20movement%20of%20refugees%20from%20West%20Punjab%20into%20Jammu%2C%20the%20Poonch%20revolt%20against%20the%20Maharaja%20and%20the%20armed%20tribals%20entering%20the%20state%20with%20the%20connivance%20and%20support%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20authorities%2C%20forcing%20the%20Maharaja%20to%20send%20a%20desperate%20distress%20appeal%20for%20help%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India.%20The%20exact%20chronology%20of%20events%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20speculation%20and%20academic%20debate%2C%20in%20the%20light%20of%20fuzzy%20evidence%20but%20what%20is%20significant%20is%20that%20all%20of%20these%20factors%20were%20co-related%20and%20had%20a%20direct%20or%20indirect%20bearing%20on%20the%20other%2C%20engendering%20tensions%20and%20creating%20divisive%20fault%20lines%20that%20would%20become%20part%20and%20parcel%20of%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20destiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10173044%2Fimage-1598.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22981%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10173044%2Fimage-1598.png%20588w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10173044%2Fimage-1598-300x228.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688501%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22744%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMaharaj%20Hari%20Singh%2C%20last%20ruler%20of%20Kashmir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInstrument%20of%20Accession%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20armed%20tribals%20from%20North%20West%20Frontier%20province%20entered%20Kashmir%2C%20Indian%20minister%20V.P.%20Menon%20flew%20to%20Srinagar%20where%20he%20met%20the%20Maharaja%20on%20October%2026%2C%201947%20and%20both%20left%20Srinagar%20for%20Delhi%20where%20Menon%20reported%20to%20the%20defense%20committee%20that%20the%20only%20basis%20of%20sending%20troops%20into%20an%20independent%20country%20had%20to%20be%20accession.%20He%20also%20opined%20that%20in%20view%20of%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20population%2C%20accession%20should%20be%20conditional%20on%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20being%20ascertained%20after%20the%20raiders%20have%20been%20driven%20out%20of%20the%20state%20and%20law%20and%20order%20have%20been%20restored.%20After%20this%20meeting%20it%20was%20decided%20that%20the%20accession%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20should%20be%20accepted%20subject%20to%20the%20proviso%20that%20a%20plebiscite%20would%20be%20held%20in%20the%20state%20when%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation%20allowed%20this%20decision.%20This%20had%20the%20fullest%20support%20of%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%2C%20noted%20Menon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20circumstances%20of%20accession%20were%20peculiar.%20The%20Hindu%20Maharaja%20of%20the%20Muslim%20majority%20state%20had%20initially%20wanted%20to%20stay%20independent.%20He%20signed%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20on%20October%2026%2C%201947%2C%20after%20Pashtun%20tribals%20aided%20by%20Pakistan%20invaded%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20India%20agreed%20to%20help%20only%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20accession.%20The%20Schedule%20appended%20to%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20clearly%20gave%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%20power%20to%20legislate%20for%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20on%20only%20three%20subjects%20%E2%80%93%20defence%2C%20external%20affairs%20and%20communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaizan%20Mustafa%20writes%2C%20In%20Clause%205%20of%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%2C%20Hari%20Singh%20said%20that%20the%20terms%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmy%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20cannot%20be%20varied%20by%20any%20amendment%20of%20the%20Act%20or%20of%20The%20Indian%20Independence%20Act%20unless%20such%20amendment%20is%20accepted%20by%20me%20by%20an%20Instrument%20supplementary%20to%20this%20Instrument%E2%80%9D.%20In%20Clause%207%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CNothing%20in%20this%20Instrument%20shall%20be%20deemed%20to%20commit%20me%20in%20any%20way%20to%20acceptance%20of%20any%20future%20Constitution%20of%20India%20or%20to%20fetter%20my%20discretion%20to%20enter%20into%20arrangements%20with%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20under%20any%20such%20future%20Constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20370%20was%20a%20constitutional%20recognition%20of%20the%20conditions%20mentioned%20in%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%2C%20and%20reflected%20the%20contractual%20rights%20and%20obligations%20of%20the%20two%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20reply%20on%20October%2027%201947%2C%20Lord%20Mountbatten%20responded%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20my%20government%E2%80%99s%20wish%20that%20as%20soon%20as%20law%20and%20order%20have%20been%20restored%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20her%20soil%20cleared%20of%20the%20invaders%2C%20the%20question%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20accession%20should%20be%20settled%20by%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EParticularities%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20accession%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENoorani%20notes%20that%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20accession%20was%20the%20only%20unique%20instance%20of%20being%20accompanied%20by%20a%20letter%20which%20the%20Maharaja%20wrote%20to%20Lord%20Mountbatten.%20The%20significant%20details%20of%20the%20letter%20state%20that%20%E2%80%9CJammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20contiguous%20to%20both%20the%20dominions%20it%20has%20vital%20economic%20and%20cultural%20links%20with%20both%20of%20them%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20points%20out%20its%20international%20strategic%20significance%20with%20proximity%20to%20Soviet%20republic%20and%20China.%20He%20mentioned%20that%20%E2%80%9Cunder%20the%20standstill%20agreement%20the%20Pakistan%20government%20was%20operating%20Posts%20and%20Telegraph%20system%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9CPakistan%20had%20tried%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20state%20to%20accede%20culminating%20in%20the%20communal%20tribal%20raids%E2%80%9D.%20It%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20the%20conditions%20obtaining%20at%20present%20in%20my%20state%20and%20the%20great%20emergency%20of%20the%20situation%20as%20it%20exists%2C%20I%20have%20no%20option%20but%20to%20ask%20for%20help%20from%20the%20Indian%20dominion.%20Naturally%20they%20cannot%20send%20the%20help%20asked%20for%20by%20me%20without%20my%20state%20acceding%20to%20the%20dominion%20of%20India%20I%20have%20accordingly%20decided%20to%20do%20so%20and%20I%20attach%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20for%20acceptance%20by%20your%20government%20the%20other%20alternative%20is%20to%20leave%20my%20state%20and%20my%20people%20to%20free%20booters.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20reply%20on%20October%2027%201947%2C%20Lord%20Mountbatten%20responded%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20my%20government%E2%80%99s%20wish%20that%20as%20soon%20as%20law%20and%20order%20have%20been%20restored%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20her%20soil%20cleared%20of%20the%20invaders%2C%20the%20question%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20accession%20should%20be%20settled%20by%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accession%20thus%20was%20not%20permanent%20and%20irrevocable.%20It%20had%20to%20be%20settled%20by%20a%20referendum%20which%20was%20principally%20agreed%20to%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20before%20and%20after%20the%20dispute%20went%20to%20United%20Nations.%20New%20Delhi%20took%20the%20case%20to%20the%20UN%20resulting%20in%20a%20UN%20resolution%20to%20resolve%20the%20dispute%20through%20a%20referendum%20after%20demilitarization%20from%20both%20sides%2C%20beginning%20with%20withdrawal%20of%20Pakistan%20Army%20from%20the%20state.%20Both%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20occupy%20the%20two%20parts%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20have%20kept%20the%20political%20dispute%20alive%2C%20giving%20rise%20to%20insurgency%20since%201989.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fsatya-pal-malik-full-interview-pulwama-modi%5C%22%3EPulwama%2C%20Modi%2C%20Corruption%3A%20Full%20Explosive%20Transcript%20of%20Satya%20Pal%20Malik%E2%80%99s%20Viral%20Interview%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArticle%20370%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2017%2C%201949%2C%20Article%20370%20was%20included%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20by%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20after%20it%20was%20moved%20for%20consideration%20as%20Article%20306A.%20In%20defence%20of%20the%20special%20status%20for%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20during%20the%20Indian%20Constituent%20Assembly%20proceedings%2C%20N.%20Gopalaswamy%20Ayyangar%20had%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20state%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20ripe%20for%20full%20integration%E2%80%9D%20and%20reasoned%20that%20a%20significant%20degree%20of%20autonomy%20had%20to%20be%20given%20within%20the%20constitutional%20structure%20of%20the%20Indian%20Union.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20effect%20of%20this%20Article%20is%20that%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20State%20which%20is%20now%20a%20part%20of%20India%2C%20will%20be%20a%20unit%20of%20the%20future%20federal%20Republic%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAyyangar%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20have%20also%20agreed%20that%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20through%20the%20instrument%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20will%20determine%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20state%20as%20well%20as%20the%20sphere%20of%20union%20jurisdiction%20over%20the%20state.%20At%20present%2C%20the%20legislature%20which%20was%20known%20as%20the%20Praja%20Sabha%20in%20the%20state%20is%20dead.%20but%20neither%20the%20legislature%20nor%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20can%20be%20convoked%20or%20can%20function%20until%20complete%20peace%20comes%20to%20prevail%20in%20that%20state.%20We%20have%20therefore%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20government%20of%20the%20state%20which%2C%20as%20represented%20in%20its%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%20reflects%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20largest%20political%20party%20in%20the%20state.%20Till%20a%20Constituent%20Assembly%20comes%20into%20being%20only%20an%20interim%20arrangement%20is%20possible%20and%20not%20an%20arrangement%20which%20could%20at%20once%20be%20brought%20into%20line%20with%20the%20arrangements%20existing%20in%20the%20case%20of%20other%20states%20now%20if%20you%20remember%20the%20viewpoints%20that%20I%20have%20mentioned%2C%20it%20is%20an%20inevitable%20conclusion%20that%2C%20at%20the%20present%20moment%2C%20we%20could%20establish%20only%20an%20interim%20system%20Article%20306A%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20establish%20such%20a%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20a%20relevant%20piece%20of%20history%20that%20Article%20370%20(then%20Article%20306A)%20was%20passed%20unanimously%20with%20only%20one%20dissenter.%20He%20was%20interestingly%20not%20the%20Hindu%20right-wing%20ideologue%2C%20Shyama%20Prasad%20Mukherjee%2C%20but%20Maulana%20Hasrat%20Mohani%2C%20founder%20of%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India.%20The%20latter%E2%80%99s%20objection%20was%20not%20to%20the%20grant%20of%20special%20status%20to%20Kashmir%20but%20he%20was%20seeking%20similar%20models%20of%20autonomy%20for%20all%20other%20states%20of%20India%20in%20pursuance%20of%20his%20concept%20of%20federalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10173258%2Fimage-1599-300x188.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10173258%2Fimage-1599-300x188.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F10173258%2Fimage-1599.png%20597w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688502%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22188%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20file%20photo%20of%20Hindustan%20Times%20on%20October%2026%2C%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPromise%20of%20referendum%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commitments%20to%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20special%20status%20and%20promise%20of%20a%20referendum%20were%20reiterated%20several%20times%2C%20thereafter.%20At%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20June%2011%2C%201951%2C%20Nehru%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20have%20made%20it%20perfectly%20clear%20that%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20of%20Kashmir%20was%20not%20meant%20and%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20come%20in%20the%20way%20of%20any%20decision%20which%20might%20flow%20ultimately%20from%20the%20security%20council%E2%80%99s%20decisions%E2%80%9D%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20another%20press%20conference%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20June%2021%2C%201952%20Nehru%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%20Security%20Council%20asked%20us%20about%20it%20we%20made%20it%20clear%20to%20the%20council%20again%20that%20the%20Kashmir%20government%20had%20every%20right%20to%20have%20a%20constituent%20assembly%20to%20frame%20the%20internal%20constitution%20but%20so%20far%20as%20we%20were%20concerned%20we%20would%20not%20be%20bound%20by%20their%20decision%20on%20the%20question%20before%20the%20Security%20Council%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%20in%20a%20speech%20delivered%20by%20Nehru%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%2026th%20June%201952%2C%20Nehru%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CLet%20us%20suppose%20there%20was%20a%20proper%20plebiscite%20there%20and%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20said%20%E2%80%98we%20do%20not%20want%20to%20be%20with%20India%E2%80%99.%20Well%2C%20we%20are%20committed%20to%20it.%20We%20would%20accept%20it.%20It%20might%20pain%20us%20but%20we%20would%20not%20send%20an%20army%20against%20them.%20We%20might%20accept%20that%2C%20however%2C%20much%20hurt%20we%20might%20feel%20about%20it%20and%20we%20would%20change%20our%20constitution%20about%20it.%E2%80%9D%20In%20another%20important%20speech%20in%20the%20parliament%20on%207th%20August%201952%2C%20Nehru%20again%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20want%20to%20win%20people%20against%20their%20will%20and%20with%20the%20help%20of%20armed%20force%20and%20if%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20state%20so%20wish%20it%20to%20part%20company%20from%20us%2C%20they%20can%20go%20their%20way%20and%20we%20shall%20go%20our%20way.%20We%20want%20no%20forced%20marriages%20no%20forced%20unions%20like%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20scholar%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-article-370-has-not-been-scrapped-but-kashmirs-special-status-has-gone-5880390%2F%5C%22%3EFaizan%20Mustafa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CSome%20critics%20of%20Article%20370%20have%20argued%20that%20Kashmir%20joined%20India%20in%201947%20without%20any%20conditions%2C%20and%20Article%20370%20unnecessarily%20gave%20it%20special%20status.%20However%2C%20the%20drafting%20of%20the%20Constitution%20ended%20on%20November%2026%2C%201949%20%E2%80%94%20Article%20370%20had%20been%20included%20before%20the%20Constitution%20was%20adopted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConciliation%20and%20resolution%2C%20however%2C%20always%20remained%20peppered%20with%20mutual%20suspicions.%20Attempts%20to%20resolve%20Kashmir%20dispute%20came%20a%20cropper%20right%20in%20the%20beginning.%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Pakistan%20issued%20a%20joint%20communique%20on%20August%2021%2C1953%20to%20reiterate%20their%20commitment%20to%20holding%20a%20plebiscite%20on%20Kashmir%20and%20decided%20that%20the%20plebiscite%20administrator%20should%20be%20appointed%20by%20April%201954.%20Both%20the%20prime%20ministers%20of%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20took%20keen%20interests%2C%20following%20this%20significant%20communique%20with%20further%20correspondence%20and%20were%20nearing%20an%20agreement%20both%20with%20regard%20to%20a%20regional%20plebiscite%20and%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20plebiscite%20administration%20to%20be%20selected%20from%20an%20Asian%20State%20but%20signs%20of%20discord%20soon%20appeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApparently%2C%20Nehru%20developed%20cold%20feet%20on%20the%20news%20of%20massive%20US%20aid%20for%20Pakistan%20and%20negotiations%20for%20a%20military%20pact%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20United%20States%2C%20invoking%20fears%20in%20New%20Delhi%20that%20United%20States%20would%20interfere%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20question.%20Nehru%20conveyed%20his%20apprehensions%20to%20Pakistan%20but%20even%20after%20the%20US-Pakistan%20pact%20was%20signed%20on%20May%2015%2C%201954%20Nehru%20said%20India%20still%20stands%20by%20her%20international%20commitments%20on%20the%20Kashmir%20issue%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20implement%20them%20at%20the%20appropriate%20time.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20statements%20pointing%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20reiteration%20of%20commitment%20towards%20referendum%20and%20settlement%20of%20Kashmir%20dispute%20are%20indications%20of%20the%20legality%20of%20Kashmir%20dispute.%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20accession%20to%20India%20and%20its%20consequent%20constitutional%20status%20were%20thus%20only%20interim%20arrangements.%20Article%20370%20was%20temporary%20only%20till%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20could%20modify%2C%20retain%20or%20reject%20it.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Kashmir%20before%20adjourning%20sine%20die%20in%201957%20decided%20to%20retain%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20scholar%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-article-370-has-not-been-scrapped-but-kashmirs-special-status-has-gone-5880390%2F%5C%22%3EFaizan%20Mustafa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CSome%20critics%20of%20Article%20370%20have%20argued%20that%20Kashmir%20joined%20India%20in%201947%20without%20any%20conditions%2C%20and%20Article%20370%20unnecessarily%20gave%20it%20special%20status.%20However%2C%20the%20drafting%20of%20the%20Constitution%20ended%20on%20November%2026%2C%201949%20%E2%80%94%20Article%20370%20had%20been%20included%20before%20the%20Constitution%20was%20adopted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkashmir-the-second-laboratory-of-hindutva-nationalism%5C%22%3EKashmir%2C%20the%20Second%20Laboratory%20of%20Hindutva%20Nationalism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInevitability%20of%20special%20status%20and%20anxieties%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20need%20to%20recognize%20the%20special%20status%20in%20view%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20partition%20and%20the%20history%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20coupled%20with%20the%20unique%20circumstances%20of%20its%20accession%20continued%20to%20be%20felt%20even%20as%20New%20Delhi%20remained%20uneasy%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20majority%20status%20in%20conjunction%20with%20the%20hostile%20journey%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan.%20The%20anxieties%20of%20the%20Muslims%20living%20within%20were%20reciprocal%20like%20Newton%E2%80%99s%20third%20law%20of%20motion%3B%20and%20both%20these%20eventually%20began%20to%20shape%20the%20aspirations%20and%20desires%20of%20the%20minorities%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20The%20Indian%20state%20was%20not%20only%20mindful%20of%20both.%20It%20played%20up%20the%20latter%20to%20counter%20the%20former.%20But%20before%20that%20happened%2C%20Nehru%20was%20guided%20by%20the%20moral%20and%20democratic%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdullah%2C%20who%20had%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20conditional%20accession%20with%20India%20had%20expressed%20fears%20about%20the%20future%20of%20a%20Muslim%20majority%20region%20in%20India%2C%20thus%2C%20earning%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20mistrust.%20When%20the%20Sheikh%20brought%20plebiscite%20demand%20out%20of%20the%20bag%2C%20it%20was%20a%20red%20herring%20for%20Nehru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20A.G.%20Noorani%2C%20the%201952%20Delhi%20Agreement%2C%20between%20then%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Kashmiri%20leader%20Shiekh%20Mohammad%20Abdullah%2C%20has%20explicitly%20given%20the%20solemn%20pledge%20to%20protect%20identity%20and%20culture%20of%20Kashmiri%20people%20by%20preventing%20outsiders%20to%20own%20land%20in%20the%20disputed%20region%20as%20well%20as%20to%20protect%20its%20demographic%20character%20in%20the%20Hindu%20majority%20India%2C%20an%20identical%20reason%20that%20compelled%20Hindu%20ruler%20to%20enact%20the%20law%20in%201923.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20the%20present%20government%20of%20Kashmir%20is%20very%20anxious%20to%20preserve%20that%20right%20because%20they%20are%20afraid%2C%20and%20I%20think%20rightly%20afraid%2C%20that%20Kashmir%20would%20be%20overrun%20by%20people%20whose%20sole%20qualification%20might%20be%20the%20possession%20of%20too%20much%20money%20and%20nothing%20else%2C%20who%20might%20buy%20up%2C%20and%20get%20the%20delectable%20places.%20So%2C%20we%20agreed%20and%20noted%20this%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nehru%20told%20Indian%20parliament%20in%201952.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdullah%2C%20who%20had%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20conditional%20accession%20with%20India%20had%20expressed%20fears%20about%20the%20future%20of%20a%20Muslim%20majority%20region%20in%20India%2C%20thus%2C%20earning%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20mistrust.%20When%20the%20Sheikh%20brought%20plebiscite%20demand%20out%20of%20the%20bag%2C%20it%20was%20a%20red%20herring%20for%20Nehru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EErosion%20of%20Article%20370%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20mutual%20anxieties%20and%20insecurities%20prompted%20New%20Delhi%20to%20manipulate%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20politics%20and%20continuously%20make%20attempts%20to%20erode%20its%20special%20status%20and%20hollow%20out%20Article%20370%20after%20Sheikh%E2%80%99s%20deposition%20and%20arrest.%20The%20Presidential%20Order%20of%201954%20and%20subsequent%20orders%20allowed%20the%20extension%20of%20almost%20the%20entire%20Indian%20Constitution%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENinety-four%20out%20of%2097%20entries%20in%20the%20Union%20List%20were%20applicable%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20260%20out%20of%20the%20395%20Articles%20of%20the%20Constitution%20as%20well%20as%207%20out%20of%20the%2012%20Schedules%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20were%20extended%20to%20the%20state%20before%20the%20Article%20370%20was%20completely%20decimated%20on%20August%205%2C%202019.%20Article%2035%20A%2C%20which%20defined%20the%20classes%20of%20persons%20who%20are%2C%20or%20shall%20be%2C%20permanent%20residents%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%3B%20or%20conferring%20on%20such%20permanent%20residents%20any%20special%20rights%20like%20employment%20in%20the%20state%20government%20and%20acquisition%20of%20immovable%20property%2C%20came%20into%20being%20through%20one%20such%20presidential%20order%20but%20only%20to%20lend%20clarity%20to%20the%20definition%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98permanent%20resident%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20enacted%20the%20Constitution%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20which%20accepted%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20position%20as%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20India%20while%20retaining%20the%20special%20status%20provided%20under%20Article%20370.%20It%20also%20barred%20on%20the%20future%20Legislative%20Assembly%20from%20interfering%20with%20the%20constitutional%20relationship%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20Union.%20The%20full%20and%20final%20seal%20to%20Article%20370%20was%20stamped%20making%20it%20irrevocable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20Article%20370%20temporary%20or%20irrevocable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20common%20myth%20with%20respect%20to%20Article%20370%20is%20that%20it%20was%20temporary%20and%20thus%20could%20have%20been%20revoked%20any%20time.%20According%20to%20the%20constitution%2C%20Article%20370%20was%20a%20temporary%20provision%20in%20the%20Constitution%20to%20govern%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Union%20but%20only%20till%20such%20time%20as%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20met%20to%20determine%20the%20exact%20nature%20of%20the%20relationship.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20enacted%20the%20Constitution%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20which%20accepted%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20position%20as%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20India%20while%20retaining%20the%20special%20status%20provided%20under%20Article%20370.%20It%20also%20barred%20on%20the%20future%20Legislative%20Assembly%20from%20interfering%20with%20the%20constitutional%20relationship%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20Union.%20The%20full%20and%20final%20seal%20to%20Article%20370%20was%20stamped%20making%20it%20irrevocable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Constituent%20Assembly%20adopted%20a%20Constitution%20on%20November%2017%2C%201956%2C%20to%20come%20into%20force%20on%20January%2026%2C%201957.%20Its%20Article%203%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20State%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20and%20shall%20be%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20Union%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%20Article%204%20lays%20down%20that%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20State%20shall%20comprise%20of%20the%20territories%20which%20on%20the%2015%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20of%20August%201947%20were%20under%20the%20sovereignty%20or%20suzerainty%20of%20the%20ruler%20of%20the%20State.%20It%20was%20also%20decided%20that%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20would%20consist%20of%20100%20members%20and%2025%20seats%20were%20to%20be%20left%20vacant%20%E2%80%9Cuntil%20the%20area%20of%20the%20State%20under%20the%20occupation%20of%20Pakistan%20ceases%20to%20be%20occupied%E2%80%A6..%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20court%20rulings%20in%20recent%20years%20are%20illustrative%20of%20the%20fact.%20In%202016%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20acknowledged%20the%20special%20status%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20reaffirmed%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20not%20temporary.%20The%20court%20observed%20that%20Article%20370%20cannot%20be%20repealed%20without%20the%20concurrence%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20In%202017%2C%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20rejected%20a%20petition%20that%20argued%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20temporary%2C%20and%20that%20its%20continuation%20was%20a%20fraud%20on%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20same%20year%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20said%20that%20due%20to%20historical%20reasons%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20a%20special%20status.%20In%20April%202018%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20that%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Ctemporary%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20headnote%20notwithstanding%2C%20Article%20370%20was%20not%20temporary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdicts%20prior%20to%20these%20were%20also%20on%20similar%20lines.%20In%20the%20famous%201968%20case%20of%20Sampat%20Prakash%20versus%20State%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20decided%20that%20Article%20370%20could%20be%20invoked%20even%20after%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20%E2%80%9CArticle%20370%20has%20never%20ceased%20to%20be%20operative%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20laid%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJ%26amp%3BK%20Reorganisation%20Act%20(August%205%2C%202019)%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20watering%20down%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20re-orientation%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20state%2C%20its%20division%20and%20creation%20of%20two%20separate%20union%20territories%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%20thus%20brings%20into%20focus%20the%20legality%20of%20such%20a%20move%2C%20as%20is%20argued%20by%20constitutional%20jurists.%20The%20manner%20in%20which%20this%20was%20done%20raises%20questions%20of%20constitutional%2C%20moral%20and%20democratic%20propriety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%20the%20constitutional%20changes%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20were%20brought%20by%20a%20Presidential%20Order%20272%2C%20a%20statutory%20resolution%20in%20the%20parliament%20that%20recommended%20the%20president%20to%20de-operationalise%20Article%20370%20and%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reorganisation%20Act%20that%20broke%20up%20the%20state%20into%20Union%20Territories%20of%20Ladakh%2C%20without%20a%20legislature%2C%20and%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20with%20an%20emasculated%20legislature%2C%20under%20two%20all-powerful%20Lieutenant%20Governors%2C%20enabling%20Central%20Government%20to%20directly%20rule%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20this%20presidential%20order%2C%20the%20concurrence%20of%20the%20government%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20been%20taken.%20However%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20under%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20and%20thus%20the%20consent%20taken%20was%20that%20of%20the%20Governor%2C%20virtually%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20central%20government.%20This%20was%20a%20case%20of%20the%20Centre%20taking%20its%20own%20consent%20to%20amend%20the%20constitution.%20This%20was%20%3Cem%3Eultra%20vires%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20constitutional%20provision%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20according%20to%20whose%20Clause%203%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20was%20imperative%20to%20make%20any%20amendments.%20However%2C%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20ceased%20functioning%20in%201957.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20President%20invoked%20modification%20powers%20under%20Article%20370%20by%20issuing%20the%20Constitution%20(Application%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir)%20Order%2C%202019%20to%20substitute%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20the%20state%20with%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20the%20state%2C%20thereby%20removing%20the%20constitutional%20requirement%20to%20convene%20a%20newly%20elected%20Constituent%20Assembly%20to%20determine%20the%20future%20of%20Article%20370.%20Since%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%20under%20Article%20356%20was%20in%20operation%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20government%20argued%20that%20Parliament%20can%20act%20as%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20while%20recommending%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Presidential%20order%20adds%20a%20sub-clause%20to%20Article%20376%2C%20replacing%20the%20terms%20%E2%80%9CConstituent%20assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D%20to%20mean%20%E2%80%9Clegislative%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D%20to%20mean%20%E2%80%9Cgovernor%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20acting%20on%20the%20aid%20and%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Presidential%20order%20also%20requires%20the%20concurrence%20of%20the%20government%20of%20the%20state.%20But%20since%20the%20state%20at%20that%20time%20was%20under%20presidential%20rule%2C%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20Governor%2C%20an%20appointee%20of%20the%20Centre%2C%20is%20meaningless%20as%20it%20virtually%20means%20that%20the%20government%20is%20taking%20its%20own%20consent%20to%20radically%20alter%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20experts%20on%20Article%20370%20revocation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20the%20words%20can%20be%20replaced%2C%20it%20breaches%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20provision.%20The%20Constituent%20assembly%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20is%20essentially%20to%20include%20the%20key%20stakeholder%E2%80%99s%20voice%20while%20making%20substantial%20changes%20to%20Article%20370.%20The%20Centre%20cannot%20do%20so%20unilaterally%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20senior%20advocate%20Raju%20Ramachandran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20State%20is%20under%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20Article%20356%20(1)%20(b)%20empowers%20the%20President%20to%20vest%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20the%20state%20with%20the%20Parliament.%20But%20these%20powers%20are%20an%20interim%20arrangement%20for%20the%20enactment%20of%20laws%20till%20a%20new%20Legislative%20Assembly%20is%20elected%2C%20so%20that%20the%20state%20is%20not%20adversely%20affected%20due%20to%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20Assembly.%20The%20consent%20required%20under%20Article%20370%20(3)%20is%20not%20routine%20legislative%20power.%20It%20is%20a%20constituent%20power%20which%20determines%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20constitutional%20relationship%20between%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaizan%20Mustafa%20argues%20that%20the%20presidential%20orders%20were%20issued%20against%20the%20letter%20and%20spirit%20of%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20and%20that%20the%20August%205%2C%202019%20were%20%E2%80%9Ca%20negation%20of%20the%20constitutional%20compact%E2%80%9D%20signed%20between%20India%20and%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Maharaja.%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20acceded%20to%20India%20in%201947%2C%20only%20on%20three%20subjects%20%E2%80%93%20defence%2C%20foreign%20affairs%20and%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20Central%20Government%20did%20was%20to%20use%20Article%20367%20which%20provides%20various%20guidelines%20about%20how%20the%20Constitution%20may%20be%20interpreted%20to%20remove%20the%20necessity%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20constituent%20Assembly%E2%80%99s%20consent%20from%20Clause%203%20of%20Article%20370.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20used%20to%20amend%20Article%20367%20eventually%20to%20amend%20the%20Article%20370%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGautam%20Bhatia%2C%20clarifies%2C%20%E2%80%9C370(1)(d)%20makes%20it%20even%20clearer%20where%20it%20refers%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cother%20provisions%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Constitution%20that%20may%20be%20altered%20by%20Presidential%20Order%20(and%20this%20is%20how%20the%20present%20Presidential%20Order%20is%20different%20from%20previous%20ones%2C%20such%20as%20those%20that%20introduced%20Article%2035A).%20Article%20370%20itself%2C%20therefore%2C%20cannot%20be%20amended%20by%20a%20Presidential%20Order.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20interpretation%20of%20the%20special%20provision%20was%20altered%20to%20dilute%20the%20very%20provision%20and%20wipe%20it%20out%20without%20fulfilling%20the%20requirements%20under%20Clause%203%20of%20Article%20370.%20What%20the%20BJP%20government%20did%20by%20bringing%20a%20presidential%20order%2C%20a%20resolution%20and%20a%20bill%20to%20reorganize%20the%20state%20in%20the%20parliament%20on%20August%205%20is%20to%20invoke%20modification%20powers%20under%20Article%20370%20to%20substitute%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20the%20state%20with%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20the%20state%2C%20thereby%20removing%20the%20constitutional%20requirement%20to%20convene%20a%20newly%20elected%20Constituent%20Assembly%20to%20determine%20the%20future%20of%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaizan%20Mustafa%20argues%20that%20the%20presidential%20orders%20were%20issued%20against%20the%20letter%20and%20spirit%20of%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20and%20that%20the%20August%205%2C%202019%20were%20%E2%80%9Ca%20negation%20of%20the%20constitutional%20compact%E2%80%9D%20signed%20between%20India%20and%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Maharaja.%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20acceded%20to%20India%20in%201947%2C%20only%20on%20three%20subjects%20%E2%80%93%20defence%2C%20foreign%20affairs%20and%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20370%20limited%20the%20application%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20Under%20Article%20370(1)(d)%2C%20constitutional%20provisions%20could%20be%20applied%20to%20the%20state%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20as%20modified%20by%20the%20President%20through%20a%20Presidential%20Order%2C%20and%20upon%20the%20concurrence%20of%20the%20state%20government%20(this%20was%20the%20basis%20for%20the%20controversial%20Article%2035A%2C%20for%20example).%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2019%2F08%2F05%2Fthe-article-370-amendments-key-legal-issues%2F%5C%22%3EGautam%20Bhatia%3C%2Fa%3E%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CPerhaps%20the%20most%20important%20part%20of%20370%20was%20the%20proviso%20to%20clause%203.%20Clause%203%20itself%20authorised%20the%20President%20to%20pass%20an%20order%20removing%20or%20modifying%20parts%20of%20Article%20370.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proviso%20stated%20that%3A%20%3Cem%3EProvided%20that%20the%20recommendation%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Ethe%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20the%20State%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%20referred%20to%20in%20clause%20(2)%20shall%20be%20necessary%20before%20the%20President%20issues%20such%20a%20notification.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20effectively%2C%20in%20view%20of%20dissolution%20of%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20which%20is%20under%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20the%20government%20arrogated%20the%20right%20of%20the%20assembly%20to%20the%20Parliament%2C%20where%20the%20BJP%20enjoys%20absolute%20majority.%20The%20August%205%20changes%20were%20based%20on%20this%20flawed%20premise%20of%20deeming%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Governor%20as%20the%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20substitute%20for%20Constituent%20Assembly%20or%20even%20legislative%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20presidential%20rule%20is%20temporary%20and%20therefore%20changes%20of%20permanent%20character%20like%20constitutional%20amendments%20without%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20elected%20legislative%20assembly%20amounts%20to%20a%20constitutional%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%2C%20senior%20advocate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcaravanmagazine.in%2Flaw%2Fobviating-the-framework-of-article-370-is-intentionally-mala-fide-senior-advocate-rajeev-dhavan%5C%22%3ERajeev%20Dhavan%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20order%20seeks%20to%20supersede%20a%20constitution%E2%80%94Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20a%20constitution%20devised%20by%20a%20constituent%20assembly.%20Therefore%2C%20Article%20370%20came%20into%20being%20%5Bin%201950%5D%20while%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20not%20established%20its%20constitution.%20Article%20370%20was%20transitional%20only%20to%20the%20extent%2C%20and%20until%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20constitution%20came%20into%20place%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20constitution%20%5Bformed%5D%20by%20an%20independent%20constituent%20assembly%20is%20a%20fact%E2%80%94it%20is%20a%20legal%20fact%2C%20a%20spatial%20fact%20and%20a%20temporal%20fact.%20You%20cannot%20abolish%20it%2C%20as%20simple%20as%20that%E2%80%94it%20does%20not%20grow%20out%20of%20the%20%5BThe%20presidential%5D%20order.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20view%20was%20shared%20by%20legal%20expert%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aa.com.tr%2Fen%2Fasia-pacific%2Findia-s-move-sans-kashmir-assembly-s-say-illegal-expert%2F1553228%5C%22%3EA.G.%20Noorani%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20has%20authored%20a%20book%20on%20Article%20370%2C%20among%20several%20other%20books%20on%20Kashmir.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20abrogate%20Article%20370%20had%20vanished%20after%20the%20dissolution%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Constituent%20Assembly%20in%201956.%20Article%20370%20was%20meant%20to%20express%20the%20identity%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20because%20of%20the%20special%20circumstances%2C%20in%20which%20it%20acceded%20to%20India.%20And%20that%20identity%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20destroyed.%20It%20got%20a%20special%20status%20because%20of%20the%20historical%20circumstances%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmphasising%20that%20the%20Indian%20parliament%20was%20not%20empowered%20to%20either%20amend%20or%20delete%20the%20provision%2C%20Noorani%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20this%2C%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20State%E2%80%99s%20Constituent%20Assembly%20was%20necessary.%20Any%20concurrence%20of%20the%20state%20government%20is%20always%20subject%20to%20the%20elected%20assembly%E2%80%99s%20final%20approval.%20When%20the%20state%20is%20under%20governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20or%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20neither%20can%20accord%20that%20concurrence%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Centre%20cannot%20acquire%20concurrence%20from%20its%20own%20handpicked%20appointee%20(Governor)%20removable%20at%20will%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20in%20an%20article%20and%20termed%20the%20action%20by%20Indian%20government%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20and%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20its%20own%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constituent%20assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20did%20not%20exist%20on%20August%205%2C%202019.%20The%20legislative%20assembly%20was%20dissolved.%C2%A0%20No%20consultations%20were%20ever%20held%20with%20any%20of%20the%20stakeholders%20turning%20this%20exercise%20into%20something%20that%20invokes%20a%20sense%20of%20humiliation%20among%20its%20citizens.%20Not%20only%20were%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20special%20status%20rights%20snatched%2C%20they%20were%20also%20divided%20and%20granted%20a%20status%20that%20was%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20status%20of%20a%20fully%20integrated%20state%20in%20this%20forced%20integration%20process%20as%20per%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Re-Organisation%20Act%20that%20was%20subsequently%20passed%20on%20August%209%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20four%20grounds%20to%20believe%20this%20assertion%20to%20be%20reasonably%20true.%C2%A0%201)%20The%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20with%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20finalized%20with%20the%20provision%20of%20Article%20370%20in%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%202)%20The%20Bill%20was%20not%20referred%20by%20the%20President%20to%20the%20state%20assembly%203)%20Governor%20is%20neither%20an%20equivalent%20of%20constituent%20assembly%20or%20legislative%20assembly%20and%20thus%20cannot%20arrogate%20on%20himself%20the%20legislative%20powers%20of%20the%20state%20government.%204)%20The%20illegitimacy%20of%20using%20Article%20370%20to%20amend%20Article%20367%20which%20in%20turn%20is%20used%20to%20completely%20make%20Article%20370%20redundant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20Congress%20leader%2C%20parliamentarian%20and%20lawyer%2C%20Manish%20Tewari%2C%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FKnGRm21jfIQ%5C%22%3Einterview%20with%20Kashmir%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20that%20the%20grounds%20for%20bringing%20down%20Article%20370%20was%20laid%20down%20in%20December%202018%20when%20the%20presidential%20proclamation%2C%20announcing%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkashmirtimes.com%2Fin-conversation-with-anuradha-bhasin-nehru-in-un-jk-laws-elections-interview-with-manish-tewari-congressmp%2F%5C%22%3Esuspended%20proviso%202%20of%20Article%203%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20said%20that%20this%20was%20unique%20and%20removed%20the%20mandatory%20provision%20of%20consultation%20with%20the%20state%20legislature%20before%20re-organisation%20of%20any%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJ%26amp%3BK%20residents%20stripped%20of%20agency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20370%20was%20amended%2C%20not%20revoked%2C%20neutered%20and%20made%20inoperative.%20By%20virtue%20of%20this%20dilution%2C%20all%20the%20Presidential%20Orders%20since%201950%2C%20including%20Article%2035A%20that%20defined%20who%20a%20permanent%20resident%20is%2C%20protected%20the%20Muslim%20majority%20status%20of%20the%20state%20and%20protected%20the%20exclusive%20land%20rights%20of%20all%20its%20citizens%2C%20stood%20invalidated%2C%20and%20Indian%20constitution%20was%20extended%20to%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20truncated%20and%20demoted%20into%20two%20union%20territories%20in%20toto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constituent%20assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20did%20not%20exist%20on%20August%205%2C%202019.%20The%20legislative%20assembly%20was%20dissolved.%C2%A0%20No%20consultations%20were%20ever%20held%20with%20any%20of%20the%20stakeholders%20turning%20this%20exercise%20into%20something%20that%20invokes%20a%20sense%20of%20humiliation%20among%20its%20citizens.%20Not%20only%20were%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20special%20status%20rights%20snatched%2C%20they%20were%20also%20divided%20and%20granted%20a%20status%20that%20was%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20status%20of%20a%20fully%20integrated%20state%20in%20this%20forced%20integration%20process%20as%20per%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Re-Organisation%20Act%20that%20was%20subsequently%20passed%20on%20August%209%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEffectively%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20not%20been%20consulted%20about%20their%20future%20by%20circumventing%20the%20constitutional%20provisions.%20Before%20the%20union%20home%20minister%20moved%20the%20legislation%2C%2013-14%20million%20people%20whose%20fate%20Parliament%20was%20deciding%20were%20virtually%20put%20under%20a%20siege%20with%20imposition%20of%20Section%20144%2C%20excessive%20militarization%20and%20internet%20ban.%20With%20sweeping%20arrests%20and%20detentions%2C%20civil%20rights%20kept%20under%20prolonged%20suspension%2C%20what%20was%20abrogated%20were%20the%20last%20remaining%20vestiges%20of%20democracy%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20A%20smooth%20transition%20from%20autonomy%20to%20complete%20integration%20was%20ensured%20by%20trampling%20the%20civil%20rights%20of%20its%2014%20million%20people%20under%20the%20sheer%20weight%20of%20military%20jackboots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20pretense%20of%20democracy%20was%20discarded%20in%20doing%20this%2C%20making%20the%20residents%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20feel%20emasculated%2C%20humiliated%20and%20disenfranchised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhari-krishna-kaul-stories%5C%22%3E%20The%20Weather%20in%20Kashmir%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistory%20of%20political%2C%20constitutional%20frauds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20and%20constitutional%20frauds%20on%20Kashmir%20have%20been%20part%20of%20the%20last%20seven%20decades%20as%20Article%20370%20had%20been%20hollowed%20out%20and%20reduced%2C%20as%20infamously%20mentioned%20by%20former%20prime%20minister%20Gulzari%20Lal%20Nanda%2C%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctunnel%20in%20the%20wall%E2%80%9D%2C%20mostly%20through%20presidential%20orders%20and%20often%20papered%20with%20consent%20of%20the%20state%20legislature.%20Perhaps%2C%20the%20only%20similarity%20with%20the%20present%20case%20is%20the%20gross%20constitutional%20abuse%20in%201986%20when%20the%20presidential%20order%20extended%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Article%20249%20of%20the%20Constitution%20in%20order%20to%20empower%20the%20Parliament%20to%20legislate%20on%20the%20strength%20of%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20resolution%20and%20the%20concurrence%20was%20given%20by%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20own%20appointee%2C%20the%20then%20Governor%20Jagmohan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%20similarity%20in%20the%20way%20concurrence%20was%20sought%2C%20August%205%2C%202019%20presidential%20order%20was%20distinct%20as%20it%20signalled%20the%20absolute%20demolition%20of%20the%20edifice%20on%20which%20the%20compact%20between%20India%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20founded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constitutional%20change%20also%20sets%20a%20dangerous%20precedent%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20federalism%20and%20its%20asymmetric%20federalism%20model%2C%20in%20which%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20occupied%20the%20centre-space.%20Federalism%20has%20been%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%2C%20as%20also%20upheld%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Article%20370%20was%20an%20essential%20facet%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20federalism%20because%20it%20governed%20the%20relationship%20of%20the%20Union%20with%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20August%202019%20changes%20prompted%20A%20C%20Michael%2C%20Former%20Member%20of%20Delhi%20Minorities%20Commission%20to%20remark%2C%20%E2%80%9CThrough%20same%20act%2C%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20statehood%20could%20be%20withdrawn%20by%20putting%20who%20is%20who%20of%20India%20residing%20in%20Delhi%20under%20house%20arrest.%C2%A0Same%20act%2C%20can%20be%20used%20to%20bifurcate%20states%20under%20the%20government%20of%20other%20political%20parties.%20A%20very%20dangerous%20precedence%20set%20by%20the%20present%20government%20for%20future%20governments.%C2%A0This%20is%20an%20emergency%20of%20another%20kind.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20anxieties%20of%20the%20Centre%20repeating%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20experiment%20elsewhere%20are%20deeper%20in%20several%20other%20states%20with%20certain%20special%20provisions.%20Article%2035A%20closely%20resembles%20Article%20371%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20that%20offers%20similar%20safeguards%20to%20the%20people%20of%20the%20north-eastern%20states%20with%20respect%20to%20government%20jobs%2C%20ownership%20and%20transfer%20of%20land%20and%20its%20resources.%20Under%20Article%20371A%2C%20central%20laws%20do%20not%20automatically%20apply%20to%20the%20state%20unless%20approved%20by%20its%20legislature.%20The%20state%20enjoys%20full%20autonomy%20with%20respect%20to%20customary%20practices%20and%20laws%20with%20respect%20to%20land%20ownership%20and%20its%20resources.%20Similarly%2C%20in%20Manipur%20(Article%20371C)%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20(Article%20371H)%2C%20the%20local%20laws%20safeguard%20the%20land%20and%20customary%20rights%20of%20tribals.%20With%20respect%20to%20Sikkim%20(Article%20371F)%2C%20even%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction%20has%20been%20restricted%20on%20issues%20of%20treaties.%20Ownership%20of%20property%20is%20also%20reserved%20in%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20Jharkhand%20and%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20among%20other%20states.%20Maharashtra%20and%20Gujarat%20also%20enjoy%20a%20special%20status%20under%20Article%20371.%20Under%20this%20provision%2C%20the%20President%20may%20provide%20for%20special%20responsibilities%20to%20the%20governors%20of%20the%20two%20states%20for%20establishing%20separate%20boards%20for%20Vidarbha%20and%20Marathwada%20(in%20Maharashtra)%2C%20and%20Saurashtra%20and%20Kutch%20(in%20Gujarat)%2C%20and%20equitable%20distribution%20of%20funds%20to%20these%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPratap%20Bhanu%20Mehta%20aptly%20summed%20up%20the%20stealthy%20measures%20as%20a%20new%20form%20of%20repression%20%E2%80%9Creminiscent%20of%20the%20Reichstag%20or%20Chinese%20constitutional%20ideology%20that%20sees%20federalism%20as%20an%20obstacle%20to%20a%20strong%20state%20and%20homogenous%20culture%E2%80%9D%20and%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20asymmetric%20federalism%20arrangements%20outside%20of%20Kashmir.%20He%20wrote%20that%20if%20such%20precedents%20of%20unilaterally%20declaring%20states%20to%20be%20Union%20Territory%20were%20to%20be%20applied%20elsewhere%2C%20we%20will%20simply%20become%20%E2%80%9Ca%20union%20of%20Union%20Territories%20that%20happen%20to%20be%20a%20state%20at%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20Centre.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20what%20was%20lost%20was%20not%20just%20the%20special%20status%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20with%20its%20emotive%20appeal%20but%20also%20the%20privileges%20and%20protections%20it%20gave%20to%20the%20residents%20of%20J%26amp%3BK.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20changed%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reorganisation%2C%20including%20the%20de-operationalisation%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20were%20filed%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20within%20weeks%20of%20the%20action.%20In%20July%202023%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20began%20hearings%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%20and%20reserved%20the%20judgment.%20While%20that%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20delivered%20on%20December%2011%2C%202023%2C%20the%20government%20has%20used%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reservation%20Act%20as%20basis%20for%20introducing%20sweeping%20legal%20and%20political%20changes%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20with%20far-reaching%20consequences.%20Many%20central%20laws%20have%20been%20extended%20to%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20erstwhile%20state%E2%80%99s%20own%20laws%20have%20been%20repealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20late-night%20move%20on%20March%2031%2C%202020%2C%20one%20week%20after%20the%20Covid-19%20nation-wide%20lockdown%20was%20announced%2C%20the%20Indian%20federal%20government%20announced%20the%20gazette%20notification%20altering%20over%20100%20J%26amp%3BK%20laws%20and%20totally%20repealing%20about%2030%20through%20a%20simple%20order%20called%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reorganisation%20(Adaptation%20of%20State%20Laws)%20Order%2C%202020.%20More%20laws%20have%20been%20adapted%2C%20scrapped%20and%20altered%20ever%20since%20in%20the%20most%20arbitrary%20manner.%20The%20word%20%E2%80%98permanent%20residents%E2%80%99%20was%20purged%20in%20the%20several%20clauses%20of%20various%20laws.%20More%20significantly%2C%20the%20Civil%20Services%20Recruitment%20Act%20was%20amended%20by%20replacing%20%E2%80%98permanent%20resident%E2%80%99%20with%20%E2%80%98Domicile%E2%80%99%2C%20opening%20jobs%20in%20government%20services%20to%20Indian%20citizens%20outside%20the%20erstwhile%20state.%20Automatically%2C%20the%20clauses%20in%20all%20the%20acts%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20constitution%2C%20particularly%20with%20respect%20to%20jobs%20and%20land%20ownership%2C%20which%20required%20proof%20of%20being%20permanent%20resident%20%E2%80%93%20possession%20of%20a%20PRC%20%E2%80%93%20were%20rendered%20meaningless.%20In%20October%202020%2C%20the%20government%20repealed%20or%20altered%2026%20land%20laws%20with%20far%20reaching%20consequences%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20population.%20Several%20other%20laws%20have%20been%20introduced%20since%20and%20fresh%20amendments%20were%20recently%20introduced%20or%20passed%20in%20the%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%