itra-sends-legal-notice-to-bjps-nishikant-dubey-advocate-for-false-defamatory-allegations%5C%22%3EBJP%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20take%20the%20matter%20to%20the%20speaker%2C%20and%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%2C%20who%20later%20backed%20many%20of%20Dehadrai%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20in%20an%20affidavit%20to%20the%20ethics%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDehadrai%2C%20in%20a%20detailed%20complaint%2C%20alleged%20that%20Moitra%20accepted%20bribes%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccash%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cgifts%E2%80%9D%20from%20industrialist%20Hiranandani%20to%20ask%20questions%2C%20seeking%20information%20on%20the%20Adani%20Group%2C%20a%20rival%20industrial%20conglomerate.%20He%20said%20that%20out%20of%20the%2061%20questions%20the%20TMC%20MP%20asked%20in%20the%20lower%20house%2C%2050%20were%20related%20to%20the%20Adani%20Group%20with%20an%20intent%20to%20further%20%E2%80%9CShri%20Hiranandani%E2%80%99s%20personal%20agenda%20of%20profit%20and%20business%20rivalry%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDehadrai%20mentions%20an%20instance%2C%20too%2C%20when%20Hiranandani%20got%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20agitated%20to%20the%20point%20of%20irritation%2C%20at%20the%20loss%20of%20a%20large%20energy-related%20contract%20in%20Bengal%20with%20a%20French%20energy%20corporation%20to%20the%20Adani%20Group%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20%E2%80%9Cspecifically%20instructed%E2%80%9D%20Moitra%20to%20target%20the%20Adani%20Group%20%E2%80%9Cto%20the%20point%20of%20embarrassment%20so%20that%20he%20could%20pressure%20the%20government%20into%20restoring%20contracts%20back%20to%20himself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Hiranandani%20in%20his%20affidavit%20claims%20that%20he%20first%20met%20Moitra%20in%202017%20during%20the%20Bengal%20Global%20Business%20Summit%2C%20following%20which%20they%20became%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHiranandani%20claims%20that%20he%20found%20her%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cknowledgeable%2C%20expressive%2C%20and%20outspoken%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20bright%20intellectual%20and%20one%20of%20the%20public%20representatives%20that%20thoroughly%20understands%20both%20the%20economy%20and%20business%20matters.%20However%2C%20he%20adds%20that%20after%20she%20became%20an%20MP%2C%20her%20ambitions%20knew%20no%20bounds%20and%20she%20wanted%20to%20%E2%80%9Cquickly%20make%20a%20name%20for%20herself%20at%20the%20national%20level%E2%80%9D.%20That%20%E2%80%9Cvictory%20was%20transformational%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%E2%80%9Ctheir%20interactions%20grew%20over%20time%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20says%2C%20she%20started%20asking%20for%20odds%20and%20ends%20which%20%E2%80%9Cinvolved%E2%80%9D%20his%20time.%20He%20said%20she%20would%20expect%20him%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdrop%20everything%E2%80%9D%20and%20facilitate%20her%20immediately.%20He%20adds%20that%20she%20was%20advised%20by%20her%20friends%20and%20advisors%20that%20the%20quickest%20%E2%80%9Croute%20to%20fame%20is%20by%20personally%20attacking%E2%80%9D%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20was%20her%20wont%2C%20she%20thought%20that%20the%20only%20way%20to%20attack%20Shri%20Modi%20is%20by%20attacking%20Shri%20Gautam%20Adani%20and%20his%20group%2C%20as%20both%20were%20contemporaries%2C%20and%20they%20belong%20to%20the%20same%20state%20of%20Gujarat%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hiranandani%20says%20in%20his%20affidavit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHerein%20lies%20the%20catch.%20Dehadrai%20alleges%20that%20Moitra%2C%20in%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20conduct%2C%20asked%20questions%20regarding%20the%20Adani%20Group%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20Hiranandani%20and%20even%20took%20bribes%20from%20him.%20But%20Hiranandani%20alleges%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20that%20Moitra%20asked%20questions%20not%20at%20his%20behest%20but%20to%20further%20her%20own%20political%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHiranandani%20suggests%20that%20he%20was%20compelled%20to%20assist%20Moitra%20due%20to%20his%20friendship%20with%20her.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20says%20that%20Moitra%20was%20supported%20in%20her%20endeavour%20to%20attack%20Adani%20by%20journalists%20like%20Sucheta%20Dalal%2C%20Shardul%20Shroff%2C%20Pallavi%20Shroff%2C%20and%20possibly%20international%20journalists%20from%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20whom%20she%20had%20frequent%20interactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHiranandani%20says%20that%20%E2%80%9Cover%20a%20period%20of%20time%E2%80%9D%20in%20being%20forced%20to%20help%20her%20to%20attack%20Adani%2C%20he%20expected%20some%20business%20contracts%20in%20opposition-ruled%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20one%20of%20these%20versions%20could%20be%20true.%20However%2C%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20report%20appears%20to%20have%20relied%20solely%20on%20Dehadrai%E2%80%99s%20complaint%2C%20and%20ignored%20Hiranandani%E2%80%99s%20allegations%2C%20before%20recommending%20her%20expulsion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20attempt%20to%20get%20to%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20absent%20in%20the%20report.%20Instead%2C%20the%20report%20only%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Committee%20has%20also%20taken%20cognizance%20the%20allegation%20made%20by%20the%20complainant%20to%20the%20effect%20that%20Smt.%20Moitra%20asked%20approximately%2050%20questions%2C%20out%20of%20total%2061%2C%20posted%20by%20her%20which%20shockingly%20seek%20information%2C%20with%20the%20intent%20of%20protecting%20or%20perpetuating%20business%20interests%20of%20Shri%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20and%20his%20company.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESecondly%3C%2Fb%3E%2C%20the%20committee%20also%20took%20into%20cognizance%20of%20the%20bribery%20allegations%20against%20Moitra.%20However%2C%20in%20this%20aspect%2C%20too%2C%20it%20has%20ignored%20crucial%20incongruities%20in%20the%20details%20given%20by%20Dehadrai%20and%20Hiranandani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20take%20into%20account%20Dehadrai%E2%80%99s%20account.%20Among%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgifts%E2%80%9D%20that%20Dehadrai%20alleged%20that%20Moitra%20has%20taken%20from%20Hiranandani%20were%20%E2%80%9CiPhones%2C%20diamond%20and%20emerald%20jewellery%2C%20luxury%20items%20such%20as%20scarves%20from%20Hermes%20and%20Louis%20Vuitton%2C%20about%2035%20pairs%20of%20shoes%20from%20Salvatore%20Ferragamo%2C%20dozens%20of%20bottles%20of%20expensive%20French%20and%20Italian%20wines%2C%20packets%20of%20luxury%20cosmetics%20from%20Dubai%2C%20bags%20from%20Gucci%20and%20crocodile%20leather%20bags%20from%20Berluti%2C%20regular%20delivery%20of%20packets%20of%20cash%20both%20in%20Indian%20Rupees%20and%20Pound%20Sterling%2C%20payment%20of%20salary%20to%20staff%20members%20on%20her%20rolls%2C%20extensive%20designing%20and%20technical%20support%20from%20the%20Mumbai%20Hiranandani%20construction%20department%20for%20building%E2%80%9D%20her%20official%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccash%E2%80%9D-based%20kickbacks%20are%20concerned%2C%20Dehadrai%20alleges%20that%20he%20overheard%20a%20conversation%20between%20the%20two%20on%20the%20payment%20of%20Rs%2075%20lakh%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpresumably%20for%20election%20expenses%E2%80%9D%20prior%20to%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20and%20another%20one%20regarding%20a%20payment%20of%20Rs%202%20crore%2C%20which%20was%20paid%20by%20Hiranandani%20to%20Moitra%20in%20May%202021%20to%20target%20Gautam%20Adani%20and%20the%20prime%20minister%20in%20both%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20international%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHiranandani%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20confirm%20any%20of%20the%20two%20cash%20transactions.%20He%20merely%20says%20that%20the%20TMC%20MP%20allegedly%20kept%20making%20demands%20for%20favours%20that%20he%20needed%20to%20fulfil%20%E2%80%9Cto%20remain%20in%20close%20proximity%20with%20her%20and%20get%20her%20support%E2%80%9D.%20He%20says%20that%20her%20demands%20included%20%E2%80%9Cexpensive%20luxury%20items%E2%80%9D%2C%20support%20for%20the%20renovation%20of%20her%20official%20residence%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Csecretarial%20and%20logistical%20help%E2%80%9D%20for%20her%20travels%20within%20India%20and%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20own%20deposition%2C%20Moitra%20told%20the%20committee%20members%20that%20she%20had%20taken%20exactly%20%E2%80%9Cfour%E2%80%9D%20gifts%20from%20Hiranandani%2C%20who%20also%20happened%20to%20be%20a%20friend.%20And%20that%20could%20not%20be%20construed%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbribe%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9COne%2C%20scarf%3B%20two%2C%20makeup%20from%20Baby%20Brown%20from%20Dubai%20airport%3B%20three%2C%20architect%E2%80%99s%20drawings%20of%20my%20house%20which%20was%20renovated%20by%20CPWD%20%5BCentral%20Public%20Works%20Department%5D%3B%20and%20four%2C%20a%20car%20and%20a%20driver%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20Dubai%E2%80%A6my%20questions%20are%20all%20my%20own%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoitra%20refuted%20having%20taken%20any%20%E2%80%9Ccash%E2%80%9D%20from%20Hiranandani%2C%20and%20challenged%20the%20committee%20to%20establish%20a%20cash%20trail%20if%20indeed%20allegations%20against%20her%20were%20true.%20She%20has%20also%20repeatedly%20dismissed%20these%20allegations%20as%20a%20vindictive%20retaliation%20by%20an%20acrimonious%20boyfriend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fmahua-moitras-plight-is-testament-to-the-kismet-of-women-politicians-in-india%5C%22%3EMahua%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20Plight%20Is%20Testament%20to%20the%20Kismet%20of%20Women%20Politicians%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20of%20these%20versions%20could%20be%20true%20or%20false%2C%20but%20the%20committee%2C%20yet%20again%2C%20went%20mostly%20by%20Dehadrai%E2%80%99s%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20noted%20that%20Moitra%20allegedly%20%E2%80%9Cdemanded%20favours%20including%20cash%20and%20expensive%20luxury%20items%2C%20secretarial%20and%20logistical%20help%20for%20her%20travels%2C%20while%20washing%20its%20hands%20off%20from%20a%20probe%20that%20could%20establish%20the%20alleged%20cash%20trail.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20regards%20taking%20%E2%80%98cash%E2%80%99%20from%20Shri%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20as%20a%20sequel%20to%20%E2%80%98%3Ci%3Equid%20pro%20quo%E2%80%99%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3Ethe%20Committee%20wish%20to%20candidly%20point%20out%20that%20they%20do%20not%20have%20the%20technical%20wherewithal%20and%20expertise%20to%20criminally%20investigate%20and%20unearth%20the%20%E2%80%98money%20trail%E2%80%99%20which%20is%20invariably%20the%20task%20of%20Central%20Government%20Institutions%20(sic)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted%2C%20while%20recommending%20a%20criminal%20probe%20on%20the%20alleged%20cash%20transactions%20made%20by%20Moitra%20and%20Hiranandani%20as%20part%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Ci%3Equid%20pro%20quo%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20however%2C%20in%20the%20report%2C%20the%20committee%20also%20concludes%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20view%20of%20the%20totality%20of%20the%20facts%20and%20circumstances%20of%20the%20case%2C%20the%20Committee%20are%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20the%20allegations%20of%20accepting%20illegal%20gratification%20by%20Smt.%20Mahua%20Moitra%20from%20Shri%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20have%20been%20clearly%20established%20which%20are%20undeniable%20and%20based%20on%20systematic%20deliberations%20of%20the%20Committee%20on%20Ethics.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThirdly%3C%2Fb%3E%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20inability%20of%20the%20ethics%20committee%20to%20firmly%20establish%20the%20major%20allegations%20against%20Moitra%2C%20the%20committee%20did%20not%20cross-examine%20Hiranandani.%20Moitra%20demanded%20the%20committee%20to%20summon%20Hiranandani%20but%20the%20committee%20did%20not%20pay%20any%20heed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20committee%20members%20chose%20to%20give%20the%20maximum%20emphasis%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20Moitra%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmahua-moitra-says-neither-quid-nor-quo-only-slander-all-questions-in-parliament-were-hers%5C%22%3Eshared%20her%20login%20credentials%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Hiranandani.%20The%20report%20notes%20that%20by%20sharing%20her%20user%20ID%20and%20password%20with%20a%20non-MP%2C%20in%20this%20case%20Hiranandani%2C%20could%20have%20compromised%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20portal%20contains%20a%20variety%20of%20confidential%20information%20only%20meant%20for%20MPs.%20The%20report%20also%20says%20that%20such%20an%20act%20could%20have%20made%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20members%E2%80%99%20portal%20open%20to%20breach%2C%20and%20could%20have%20been%20misused%20by%20someone%20making%20non-public%20documents%20like%20Bills%20and%20questions%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20concluded%20that%20Moitra%20had%20shared%20her%20login%20credentials%20with%20Hiranandani%20as%20it%20was%20found%20that%20her%20login%20credentials%20were%20used%20%E2%80%9C47%20times%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20same%20IP%20address%20in%20Dubai%2C%20when%20she%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20visiting%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20response%2C%20Moitra%20has%20said%20that%20most%20MPs%20let%20their%20assistants%20and%20LAMP%20fellows%20do%20logistical%20work%20like%20uploading%20of%20questions%2C%20get%20passes%2C%20and%20similar%20other%20things.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20MPs%20have%20accepted%20that%20they%20have%20little%20knowledge%20about%20the%20digital%20medium%2C%20and%20generally%20ask%20their%20assistants%20adept%20in%20handling%20computers%20to%20do%20their%20work.%20So%2C%20Moitra%20emphasised%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20MPs%20have%20shared%20their%20user%20IDs%20and%20passwords%20with%20their%20staff%2C%20and%20that%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20MPs%20do%20not%20prepare%20their%20own%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdata-rewind-a-shadow-on-parliaments-ability-to-function-independently-of-the-executive%5C%22%3EData%20Rewind%3A%20A%20Shadow%20on%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20Ability%20to%20Function%20Independently%20of%20the%20Executive%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoitra%20said%20that%20all%20MPs%20were%20like%20%E2%80%9Cconveyor%20belts%E2%80%9D%20who%20receive%20information%20from%20the%20public%20and%20prepare%20their%20questions%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20shared%20information.%20She%20said%20that%20most%20of%20the%20information%20she%20sought%20through%20her%20questions%20regarding%20the%20Adani%20Group%20could%20have%20also%20been%20accessed%20by%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20admitted%20that%20she%20had%20shared%20her%20login%20credentials%20but%20asserted%20that%20its%20use%20was%20not%20unsupervised.%20With%20each%20of%20the%20login%2C%20the%20access%20to%20the%20mandatory%20one-time%20password%20was%20only%20with%20her%20in%20her%20phone%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20login%20ID%20and%20password%20were%20shared%20with%20someone%20in%20his%20office%20to%20upload%20it.%20This%20is%20my%20statement.%20I%20have%20not%20done%20anything%20unethical%E2%80%A6The%20main%20thing%20is%20the%20supervised%20access%E2%80%A6there%20are%20no%20rules%20which%20were%20given%20to%20us%20as%20to%20who%20could%20or%20who%20could%20not%20operate%20it%E2%80%A6without%20the%20OTP%2C%20there%20is%20no%20access%E2%80%A6nobody%20can%20put%20in%20even%20a%20single%20question.%20The%20OTP%20came%20to%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20MPs%2C%20too%2C%20have%20said%20that%20many%20of%20them%20operate%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20portal%20through%20their%20assistants.%20They%20also%20believe%20that%20the%20committee%2C%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20a%20fair%20probe%2C%20should%20have%20cross-examined%20Hiranandani%2C%20too%2C%20like%20it%20did%20with%20Dehadrai%20and%20Dubey.%20In%20such%20circumstances%2C%20the%20report%20can%20only%20fuel%20speculation%20that%20the%20committee%20was%20governed%20more%20by%20vested%20political%20interests%20instead%20of%20principles%20of%20natural%20justice.%20The%20division%20among%20committee%20members%20along%20party%20lines%20only%20strengthens%20such%20conjectures.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702189383000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F03143050%2FDBTy8XrWAAAFLVI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fat-least-three-critical-flaws-in-the-ethics-committee-report-on-mahua-moitra%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20committee%20failed%20to%20establish%20the%20major%20allegations%20against%20Moitra.%20The%20versions%20presented%20by%20Dehadrai%20and%20Hiranandani%20did%20not%20match%2C%20and%20the%20committee%20also%20could%20not%20establish%20a%20cash%20trail.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20did%20not%20conduct%20a%20cross-examination%20of%20Hiranandani.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fat-least-three-critical-flaws-in-the-ethics-committee-report-on-mahua-moitra%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Is%20immigration%20'out%20of%20control'%20in%20Ireland%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702189380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F70x70%2Fskynews-ireland-immigration_6386673.jpg%3F20231208151726%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fis-immigration-to-ireland-out-of-control-many-in-the-land-of-a-hundred-thousand-welcomes-are-worried-13025649%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Iqbal%20Chaudry%20bellows%20the%20adhan%2C%20or%20Muslim%20call%20to%20prayer%2C%20as%20his%20young%20grandchildren%20Ali%2C%20five%2C%20and%20Aaleen%2C%20three%2C%20giggle%20and%20play%20on%20the%20carpeted%20floor.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A132%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fis-immigration-to-ireland-out-of-control-many-in-the-land-of-a-hundred-thousand-welcomes-are-worried-13025649%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-c