y%20increased%20substantially%20over%20the%202018%20figures%3A%20Rajasthan%20by%203.69%25%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20by%207.66%25%2C%20and%20Chattisgarh%20by%2013.37%25%3B%20even%20in%20Telangana%20(which%20it%20lost)%2C%20its%20vote%20share%20has%20gone%20up%20by%209%25.%20This%20is%20a%20psephological%20puzzle%20because%20the%20general%20consensus%20is%20that%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20brand%20equity%20is%20no%20longer%20as%20strong%20as%20it%20was%20in%202018-19%2C%20that%20the%20appeal%20of%20Hindutva%20has%20peaked%2C%20and%20that%20economic%20issues%20such%20as%20price%20rise%20and%20unemployment%20have%20begun%20to%20bite.%20What%20then%20is%20the%20generic%20explanation%20for%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20phenomenal%20rise%20in%20vote%20share%20in%202023%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20distinct%20possibility%20that%20the%20answer%20could%20lie%20in%20the%20hitherto%20ignored%20FTV.%20An%20interesting%20article%20in%20the%20New%20Indian%20Expressed%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fopinions%2F2023%2Fnov%2F25%2Fthe-seven-sins-of-new-india-2635919.html%5C%22%3EThe%20Seven%20Sins%20of%20New%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98%20by%20K.%20Jayakumar%2C%20published%20on%20November%2025%2C%20postulates%20that%20the%20young%20generation%20of%20today%20(read%20FTV)%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20no%20exposure%20to%20an%20earlier%20ethos%20of%20public%20life%2C%20begins%20to%20believe%20that%20what%20it%20sees%20today%20is%20normal.%E2%80%9D%20And%20what%20this%20generation%20sees%20today%20is%20listed%20by%20Jayakumar%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cseven%20sins%20of%20new%20India.%E2%80%9D%20These%20are%3A%20Inequality%20before%20the%20law%2C%20vindictive%20vehemence%2C%20intolerance%20to%20criticism%2C%20corruption%2C%20doublespeak%2C%20window%20dressing%2C%20and%20the%20baggage%20of%20secularism.%20These%20seven%20sins%20comprise%20the%20new%20normal%20and%20have%20changed%20the%20idiom%20of%20public%20life%20and%20polity%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20find%20this%20a%20fascinating%20thesis%2C%20one%20which%20makes%20eminent%20sense.%20Just%20step%20back%20and%20consider%3A%20the%20FTV%20of%20today%20was%20only%20eight%20years%20old%20in%202014%2C%20and%20thirteen%20in%202019.%20These%20are%20impressionable%20ages%2C%20the%20crucible%20when%20values%2C%20behaviour%2C%20beliefs%20and%20prejudices%20are%20formed.%20This%20generation%20has%20grown%20up%20in%20the%20Modi%20years%20and%20has%20seen%20nothing%20but%20the%20seven%20deadly%20sins%20in%20operation%2C%20carpet-bombed%20by%20media%20and%20party%20propaganda%20to%20believe%20in%20this%20right-wing%20ideology%20and%20that%20Modi%20is%20the%20Vishwaguru.%20They%20are%20creatures%20of%20this%20new%20toxic%20environment%2C%20and%20their%20value%20systems%20can%20only%20align%20with%20this%20new%20reality%2C%20having%20experienced%20no%20other%20one.%20I%2C%20for%20one%2C%20therefore%20would%20be%20very%20surprised%20if%20they%20did%20not%20vote%20for%20the%20BJP%20in%20elections%2C%20almost%20as%20a%20bloc.%20This%20thesis%20brings%20together%20all%20the%20anecdotal%20data%20and%20statistics%20mentioned%20above%2C%20and%20may%20go%20some%20way%20in%20explaining%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20continued%20appeal%20and%20the%20increase%20in%20its%20vote%20share.%20The%20FTV%20may%20not%20be%20the%20only%20explanation%20but%20it%20certainly%20merits%20a%20serious%20look.%20And%20the%20beauty%20of%20this%20phenomenon%20is%20that%20with%20each%20incremental%20year%20of%20this%20regime%2C%20their%20numbers%20will%20keep%20increasing%20by%20a%20few%20millions%2C%20providing%20the%20BJP%20with%20an%20ever-increasing%20constituency%20of%20programmed%20supporters.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20worse%20news%20for%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20may%20be%20wrong%20(I%20usually%20am%20in%20such%20matters)%2C%20but%20can%20the%20opposition%20continue%20to%20ignore%20the%20FTV%3F%20They%20may%20be%20their%20ticket%20to%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Favayshukla.blogspot.com%2F2023%2F12%2Fis-first-time-voter-x-factor-in-bjps.html%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20blog%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Favayshukla.blogspot.com%2F%5C%22%3EView%20from%20%5BGreater%5D%20Kailash%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20lightly%20for%20style.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702116033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09144720%2FF_IGer0XMAAJqis.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffirst-time-voters-x-factor-in-bjp-victory%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20voters%20comprise%20between%2010-15%25%20of%20the%20total%20electorate%2C%20perhaps%20more%20than%20most%20castes%20or%20religious%20denominations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffirst-time-voters-x-factor-in-bjp-victory%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20Blocked%2036%2C838%20Social%20Media%20Posts%20in%20Past%205%20Years%2C%20X-Corp%20Topped%20the%20Chart%20Among%20Platforms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15203648%2FThe-Wire-10.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EBetween%202018%20and%20October%202023%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20issued%20orders%20to%20take%20down%2036%2C838%20social%20media%20posts.%20The%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20blocked%20URLs%20relates%20to%20X%20(formerly%2C%20Twitter)%2C%20as%20a%20total%20of%2013%2C660%20posts%20were%20taken%20down%2C%20the%20government%20told%20parliament%20on%20Friday%2C%20December%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20was%20disclosed%20by%20the%20government%20in%20response%20to%20questions%20raised%20by%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20John%20Brittas%20of%20the%20CPI%20(M).%20Most%20posts%2FURLs%20(9%2C849)%20were%20taken%20down%20in%202020%2C%20the%20year%20when%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20broke%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20representing%20Kerala%2C%20sought%20to%20know%20from%20the%20government%20the%20number%20and%20details%20of%20directions%2Forders%20issued%20by%20the%20government%20during%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20under%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%20and%20Rules%20made%20thereunder%2C%20directing%20intermediaries%20and%20digital%20media%20to%20delete%2C%20modify%20or%20block%20any%20content%2C%20information%2C%20data%20or%20communication%20link.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20sought%20information%20year-wise%20and%20organisation-wise%3B%20and%20the%20number%20and%20details%20of%20directions%2Forders%20issued%20by%20the%20government%20during%20the%20last%20five%20years%20directing%20the%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20including%20Twitter%20and%20Facebook%2C%20to%20block%20or%20remove%20posts%2C%20entire%20accounts%2C%20or%20topic%20hashtags.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20the%20government%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20policies%20of%20the%20government%20are%20aimed%20at%20ensuring%20that%20the%20internet%20in%20India%20is%20open%2C%20safe%2C%20trusted%2C%20and%20accountable%20to%20all%20users.%20Accordingly%2C%20the%20government%20issues%20lawful%20directions%20for%20blocking%20access%20to%20information%20by%20the%20public%20under%20Section%2069A%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20Act%2C%202000%20which%20provides%20power%20to%20the%20government%20to%20issue%20such%20directions%20if%20it%20is%20necessary%20or%20expedient%20to%20do%20so%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%2C%20defence%20of%20India%2C%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%20friendly%20relations%20with%20foreign%20States%20or%20public%20order%20or%20for%20inciting%20cognisable%20offence%20relating%20to%20above.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20blocked%20posts%20relate%20to%20X%20(13%2C660)%2C%20it%20is%20followed%20by%20Facebook%20(10%2C197)%2C%20YouTube%20(5%2C759)%2C%20Others%20(4%2C199)%2C%20and%20Instagram%20(3%2C023).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fmusk-twitter-takedown-government-compliance%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%2C%20after%20Elon%20Musk%20took%20over%2C%20X%20Corp%20has%20been%20significantly%20more%20compliant%20with%20government%20orders%20for%20censorship%20or%20surveillance%2C%20including%20from%20India%2C%20going%20against%20Musk%E2%80%99s%20promise%20of%20ushering%20in%20a%20new%20era%20of%20free%20speech%20and%20disallowing%20political%20interference%20on%20social%20media.%20For%20instance%2C%20between%20October%2027%2C%202022%2C%20and%20April%2027%2C%202023%2C%20India%20made%2050%20requests%20which%20was%20the%20third-highest%20in%20the%20world.%20Before%20Musk%20took%20over%2C%20the%20situation%20had%20been%20largely%20different%2C%20X-Corp%20(Twitter%20then)%20contested%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20takedown%20orders%20legally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20the%20year-wise%20and%20platform-wise%20breakdown%20of%20blocked%20posts%2FURLs%3A%20%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09145553%2FEffect-22.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09145553%2FEffect-22.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09145553%2FEffect-22-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09145553%2FEffect-22-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688426%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702114505000%2C%